  <section id="overview">
  <h2>Scope and Objectives of the Workshop</h2>
  <p>
    This workshop aims to provide a focused interdisciplinary forum for researchers, practitioners, and industry stakeholders to explore how blockchain technologies and smart contracts can be effectively integrated with intelligent systems to enhance transparency, traceability, security, and trust in complex digital and cyber-physical environments. The primary objective is to examine blockchain not merely as a distributed ledger, but as a foundational trust layer that supports automated decision-making, secure data sharing, and verifiable provenance in AI-driven and data-intensive systems.
  </p>
  <p>
    By bringing together advances in smart contracts, NFTs, decentralized architectures, and intelligent algorithms, the workshop seeks to address fundamental challenges such as secure automation, accountability, anti-counterfeiting, privacy preservation, and system interoperability across heterogeneous domains.
  </p>
  <p>
    The workshop further aims to foster discussion on practical deployments, architectural trade-offs, and emerging research directions at the intersection of blockchain and intelligent systems. Particular emphasis is placed on applications involving supply-chain traceability, digital asset management, IoT and edge intelligence, decentralized and federated learning, and governance-aware intelligent services, where trust, auditability, and resilience are critical requirements. Through technical contributions, case studies, and vision papers, the workshop intends to stimulate collaboration between academia and industry, identify open challenges related to scalability, performance, and sustainability, and outline future pathways for designing secure, transparent, and intelligent decentralized systems.
  </p>
</section>

  <section id="topics">
  <h2>Topics of Interest</h2>

  <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: space-between; gap: 2rem;">
    <div style="background: #e0f2fe; padding: 1rem; border-left: 6px solid #0ea5e9; border-radius: 8px; flex: 1 1 calc(33% - 1.5rem); min-width: 280px; box-sizing: border-box;">
      <h3> <h3>üîó 1. Blockchain Foundations for Intelligent Systems</h3>
      <p><strong>Keywords:</strong> Blockchain architectures, decentralized systems, trust, transparency</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Blockchain-enabled intelligent and autonomous systems</li>
        <li>Permissioned vs. permissionless blockchains for AI-driven applications</li>
        <li>Blockchain interoperability for intelligent ecosystems</li>
        <li>Consensus mechanisms optimized for intelligent and data-driven systems</li>
        <li>Blockchain as a trust layer for intelligent decision-making</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div style="background: #fef9c3; padding: 1rem; border-left: 6px solid #eab308; border-radius: 8px; flex: 1 1 calc(33% - 1.5rem); min-width: 280px; box-sizing: border-box;">
      <h3>üìÑ 2. Smart Contracts and Automated Trust</h3>
      <p><strong>Keywords:</strong> Smart contracts, automation, security, verification</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Smart contract design for intelligent applications</li>
        <li>Formal verification and security analysis of smart contracts</li>
        <li>AI-assisted smart contract generation and auditing</li>
        <li>Smart contracts for automated compliance and governance</li>
        <li>Runtime monitoring and anomaly detection in smart contracts</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div style="background: #ede9fe; padding: 1rem; border-left: 6px solid #8b5cf6; border-radius: 8px; flex: 1 1 calc(33% - 1.5rem); min-width: 280px; box-sizing: border-box;">
      <h3>ü™ô 3. NFTs and Digital Asset Intelligence</h3>
      <p><strong>Keywords:</strong> NFTs, tokenization, digital identity, provenance</p>
      <ul>
        <li>NFTs for digital identity, ownership, and authentication</li>
        <li>Intelligent NFT systems for dynamic and programmable assets</li>
        <li>NFTs for product provenance and anti-counterfeiting</li>
        <li>Secure NFT marketplaces and fraud detection</li>
        <li>NFTs combined with AI for adaptive rights management</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    

    <div style="background: #fee2e2; padding: 1rem; border-left: 6px solid #ef4444; border-radius: 8px; flex: 1 1 calc(33% - 1.5rem); min-width: 280px; box-sizing: border-box;">
      <h3>üõ°Ô∏è 4. Security, Privacy, and Trust in Decentralized Systems</h3>
      <p><strong>Keywords:</strong> Security, privacy, trust, cryptography</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Cryptographic primitives for secure and trustworthy systems</li>
        <li>Privacy-preserving techniques (ZKPs, MPC, homomorphic encryption)</li>
        <li>Secure identity management and authentication mechanisms</li>
        <li>Attack detection and mitigation in blockchain networks</li>
        <li>Threat modeling and risk assessment for decentralized systems</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div style="background: #f0f9ff; padding: 1rem; border-left: 6px solid #0ea5e9; border-radius: 8px; flex: 1 1 calc(33% - 1.5rem); min-width: 280px; box-sizing: border-box;">
      <h3>üß† 5. Blockchain and Artificial Intelligence Integration</h3>
      <p><strong>Keywords:</strong> Intelligent systems, AI, machine learning, decentralization</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Decentralized and federated learning over blockchain</li>
        <li>Trusted data sharing for AI using blockchain</li>
        <li>Explainable AI and accountability via immutable ledgers</li>
        <li>AI-driven analytics for blockchain data</li>
        <li>Incentive mechanisms for collaborative intelligence</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div style="background: #fff7ed; padding: 1rem; border-left: 6px solid #fb923c; border-radius: 8px; flex: 1 1 calc(33% - 1.5rem); min-width: 280px; box-sizing: border-box;">
      <h3>üì° 6. IoT, Cyber-Physical, and Intelligent Edge Systems</h3>
      <p><strong>Keywords:</strong> IoT, edge intelligence, cyber-physical systems</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Blockchain for secure IoT and sensor networks</li>
        <li>Edge AI with blockchain-based coordination</li>
        <li>Secure data collection and validation from physical devices</li>
        <li>Trust management in large-scale IoT ecosystems</li>
        <li>Blockchain-enabled cyber-physical security</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div style="background: #e0f2fe; padding: 1rem; border-left: 6px solid #3b82f6; border-radius: 8px; flex: 1 1 calc(33% - 1.5rem); min-width: 280px; box-sizing: border-box;">
      <h3>‚öñÔ∏è 7. Governance, Compliance, and Ethical Intelligence</h3>
      <p><strong>Keywords:</strong> Governance, regulation, ethics, compliance</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Regulatory compliance through smart contracts</li>
        <li>Transparent governance models using blockchain</li>
        <li>Ethical challenges in intelligent and autonomous systems</li>
        <li>Auditable AI systems using immutable records</li>
        <li>Policy-aware intelligent systems</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div style="background: #fefce8; padding: 1rem; border-left: 6px solid #facc15; border-radius: 8px; flex: 1 1 calc(33% - 1.5rem); min-width: 280px; box-sizing: border-box;">
      <h3> üìà8. Performance, Scalability, and Sustainability</h3>
      <p><strong>Keywords:</strong> Scalability, performance, energy efficiency</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Scalable blockchain solutions for intelligent workloads</li>
        <li>Energy-efficient consensus and green blockchain</li>
        <li>Performance evaluation of blockchain-based intelligent systems</li>
        <li>Layer-2 solutions and off-chain computation</li>
        <li>Sustainable architectures for AI‚Äìblockchain integration</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div style="background: #ecfccb; padding: 1rem; border-left: 6px solid #65a30d; border-radius: 8px; flex: 1 1 calc(33% - 1.5rem); min-width: 280px; box-sizing: border-box;">
  <h3> üè≠ 9. Applications and Case Studies</h3>
  <p><strong>Keywords:</strong> Real-world deployment, industry use cases</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Intelligent tracking and monitoring of goods and assets</li>
    <li>Provenance verification using blockchain and AI</li>
    <li>Anti-counterfeiting technologies for luxury and industrial products</li>
    <li>Sustainable and ethical supply chains enabled by blockchain</li>
        <li>Blockchain and AI for healthcare, finance, and smart cities</li>
        <li>Intelligent transportation and logistics systems</li>
        <li>Digital twins and blockchain-based traceability</li>
        <li>Industrial case studies and pilot deployments</li>
        <li>Lessons learned from real-world implementations</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

      
